notesStmt.note: Original first gathering of folios I-VIII lacking; current first gathering, from folios IX to XVI is loose and out of order

Faye, C.U., continued and edited by W.H. Bond, Supplement to the Census of Medieval and Renaissance Manuscripts in the United States and Canada (New York: Bibliographical Society of America, 1962), p. 469, no. 21.

msContents.summary: This relatively compact Gradual was produced in Italy, apparently for the Abbey of Vollombrosa in Tuscany, in the fifteenth century. It is bound in original, exposed wooden boards. The first gathering is lacking.

supportDesc.extent: 82; 270 x 198 mm bound to 285 x 208 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Original foliation in red ink using Roman numerals, upper right margin or upper margin

p.catchwords: Horizontal catchwords in lower margin at folios: XVIv (now 4v), 20v, 26v, 34v, 64v, 72v

layoutDesc.layout: Musical notation on red, four-line staves; seven staves, with accompanying text, to a page; ruled in purple ink; written area: 215 x 150 mm

decoDesc.decoNote: Blue penwork initials heightened in red; small pen-flourished initials, alternating blue and red
Inside front coverBookplate, Library Company of Philadelphia
Inside front coverLabel, Library Company of Philadelphia

binding.p: Original wooden boards; Library Company stamp on upper cover

origin.p: According to label and two loose cards inside front cover, manuscript comes from the "Monastery of Vallombrosa, Florence"; 15th century

history.provenance: According to label and two loose cards inside front cover, manuscript was presented by "Dr. Cleborne, U.S.N."
